---
title: Homemade Lamb Keema Pau with Mango Chutney, Pickled Onion and Salad
description: Keema pau is a popular Mumbai street food. Pau (also spelt pav sometimes) is the bread part of the dish - usually pan-fried in butter or ghee. It's then loaded with a spiced lamb mince (keema means minced meat) curry.
